description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Would you like to work as an expert and leader in one of the most beautiful coastal areas in Wales? We are looking for a compassionate and experienced leader to provide direction to our paediatric speech and language therapy team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We offer a diverse range of paediatric services firmly rooted in a care aims model and underpinned by therapy outcome measures, evidence based practice and robust governance. Local partners commission a number of our paediatric services and we host regional services. There are regular departmental meetings and there is a strong senior management team and business support, as well as links across therapies. You will also play a key role deputising for the Head of Service and will need to have a clear strategic approach to service delivery.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa ChessHead of Speech and Language Therapy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;lisa.chess@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
